olive oil
1.25 cup water (for the rice)
1 packet jasmine rice
1 potato
1 carrot
2 clove garlic
½ bunch baby broccoli
20 g plant-based butter
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend
1 sachet Mumbai Spice Blend
1 sachet vegetable stock powder
1 packet coconut milk
¼ cup water (for the curry)
1 packet Baby Leaves
1 packet Crushed Peanuts
1 packet Peeled Prawns

• Preheat oven to 220°C/200°C fan-forced.
• To a medium saucepan, add the water and bring to the boil.
• Add basmati rice, stir, cover with a lid and reduce heat to low.
• Cook for 10 minutes, then remove pan from heat and keep covered until rice is tender and water is absorbed, 10 minutes.

TIP: The rice will finish cooking in its own steam so don't peek!

• Meanwhile, cut potato and carrot into bite-sized chunks.
• Place veggies on a lined oven tray. Drizzle generously with olive oil and season with salt and pepper.
• Toss to coat, spread out evenly, then roast until tender, 20-25 minutes.

• When the veggies have 15 minutes remaining, finely chop garlic. Cut baby broccoli (see ingredients) into thirds.

• In a large frying pan, heat the butter with a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook baby broccoli until softened, 5-6 minutes.
• Add garlic, mild North Indian spice blend and Mumbai spice blend and cook until fragrant, 1 minute.

• Add vegetable stock powder, coconut milk, peeled prawns and the water to the pan. Simmer until thickened, 2-4 minutes.
• Remove pan from heat, then stir through roasted veggies and baby spinach leaves until wilted. Season to taste.

TIP: Add a splash of water if the curry looks too thick!

• Divide basmati rice between plates. Top with potato, prawns and coconut curry.
• Garnish with crushed peanuts to serve. Enjoy!